{"title_page": "Ram (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 film directed by Jeethu Joseph}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ram\n| image          = Ram Movie first look.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Announcement poster \n| director       = [[Jeethu Joseph]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Ramesh P. Pillai\n* Sudhan S. Pillai\n}}\n| writer         = Jeethu Joseph\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Mohanlal]]\n* [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]]\n* [[Indrajith Sukumaran]]\n}}\n| music          = Vishnu Shyam\n| cinematography = [[Satheesh Kurup]]\n| editing        = V. S. Vinayak\n| studio         = {{plainlist|\n* Abhishek Films\n* Passion Studios\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Maxlab Cinemas and Entertainments]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|10|22}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Malayalam\n| budget         = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| gross          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n\n'''''Ram''''' is an upcoming Indian [[Malayalam]]-language [[action thriller]] film written and directed by [[Jeethu Joseph]] and produced by Abhishek Films and Passion Studios. The film stars [[Mohanlal]] in the title role, while [[Trisha]] making her second venture in [[Mollywood]] as the female lead opposite to Lal.<ref>https://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/news/mohanlal-trisha-krishnan-raam-jeethu-joseph-anoop-menon-1.4489775 </ref> [[Indrajith Sukumaran]], [[Adil Hussain]], Durga Krishnan and [[Saikumar (actor)|Saikumar]] playing important supporting roles. The film's music was composed by debutant Vishnu Shyam.\n\n[[Principal photography]] of the film began on 5 January 2020 in [[Kochi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/mohanlal-looks-super-cool-and-stylish-as-he-shoots-for-ram/articleshow/73274437.cms|title=Mohanlal looks super cool and stylish as he shoots for 'RAM' - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref> The crew are planning to shoot the film in [[Kochi]], [[Delhi]], [[Dhanushkodi]], [[Chennai]], [[Colombo]], [[London]], [[Istanbul]] and [[Cairo]]. The film is scheduled for release on Pooja 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/movie-news/mohanlal-jeethu-joseph-movie-ram-starts-rolling-1.4439514|title=Mohanlal-Jeethu Joseph movie \u2018Ram\u2019 starts rolling|website=Mathrubhumi|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Mohanlal]] as Ramchandrasekhar \"Ram\"\n* [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] as Vineetha\n* [[Indrajith Sukumaran]]\n* [[Adil Hussain]]\n*[[Vinay Forrt]] as Praveen\n* Durga Krishna as Meera\n* [[Saikumar (actor)|Saikumar]]\n* [[Suman (actor)|Suman]] as Sanjay\n* [[Leona Lishoy]]\n* [[Kalabhavan Shajohn]]\n*[[Tini Tom]]\n* [[Hima Shankar]]\n\n== Production ==\n[[Jeethu Joseph]] began the pre-production work of ''Ram'' by late 2019, while involved in the post-production work of ''[[The Body (2019 film)|The Body]]'' and ''[[Thambi (2019 film)|Thambi]]'' at the same time.<ref>{{cite news |last1=S. |first1=Srivatsan |title=Jeethu Joseph on 'Thambi', the Chinese remake of 'Drishyam' and Mohanlal's 'Ram' |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/jeethu-joseph-on-thambi-the-chinese-remake-of-drishyam-and-mohanlals-ram/article30329800.ece |accessdate=18 January 2020 |work=[[The Hindu]] |date=17 December 2019}}</ref> In September 2019, it was reported that [[Mohanlal]] and [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] will be starring in Jeethu's high-budget thriller produced by [[Chennai]]-based Abhishek Films, which is to be shot in India and abroad, with filming set to begin in November, lasting 100 days.<ref>{{cite news|author=Express News Service|title=Mohanlal, Trisha to star in director Jeethu Joseph's next film|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/sep/08/mohanlal-trisha-to-star-in-director-jeethu-josephs-next-film-2030786.html|accessdate=18 January 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=9 September 2019}}</ref> Filming date was pushed to late December, to start during the releasing week of ''Thambi''. Jeethu describes the genre as an action thriller with story set in several countries.<ref>{{cite news|last=George|first=Vijay|title=I don't want to do remakes any more: Jeethu Joseph|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/jeethu-joseph-on-his-projects-in-hindi-and-tamil-and-making-remakes/article30174996.ece|accessdate=18 January 2020|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=5 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nA [[Puja (Hinduism)|pooja]] function for the film and a press meet was held on 16 December 2019, where the film's title was revealed. While interacting to the press, Jeethu said that he was approached by the producers three years ago to make a second film with Mohanlal after ''[[Drishyam]]'' (2013), \"I was tensed about doing another film with Lalettan because it's a huge responsibility. It took me three years to come up with the right subject\". During the casting process, [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] was suggested for the role by Mohanlal.<ref>{{cite news|author=Express News Service|title=Jeethu Joseph's next with Mohanlal titled 'Ram'|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/dec/18/jeethu-josephs-next-with-mohanlal-titled-ram-2077543.html|accessdate=18 January 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=18 December 2019}}</ref> He also suggested [[Prachi Tehlan]] for another role. The film also features [[Adil Hussain]], [[Indrajith Sukumaran]], and Durga Krishna in pivotal roles.<ref>{{cite news|author=Express News Service|title=Prachi Tehlan in talks to join Mohanlal-Jeethu Joseph\u2019s 'Ram'|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2020/jan/15/prachi-tehlan-in-talks-to-join-mohanlal-jeethu-josephs-ram-2089623.html|accessdate=18 January 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\nThe music for the film is being composed by debutant Vishnu Shyam, with lyrics for the songs written by Vinayak Sasikumar.<ref>{{cite news|last=Joy|first=Joys|title=\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d37\u0d4d\u0d23\u0d41\u0d35\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d35\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d15\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d15\u0d48 \u0d15\u0d4b\u0d7c\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41; \u0d1c\u0d40\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41 \u0d1c\u0d4b\u0d38\u0d2b\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d2e\u0d4b\u0d39\u0d7b\u0d32\u0d3e\u0d7d \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02 '\u0d31\u0d3e\u0d2e\u0d3f'\u0d28\u0d41 \u0d35\u0d47\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d3f|url=https://malayalam.news18.com/news/film/lyricist-vinayak-sasikumar-and-music-director-vishnu-shyam-joins-for-jeethu-joseph-new-mohanlal-movie-ram-jj-185425.html|accessdate=18 January 2020|work=[[News18 Malayalam]]|date=16 December 2019|language=ml}}</ref> \n\n== Release ==\nThe film is planned to release on 22 October 2020 during Pooja holidays<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/mohanlal-gives-a-sneak-peek-from-the-sets-of-ram-malayalam-news-250928|title=Mohanlal gives a sneak peek from the sets of 'Ram' - Malayalam News|date=2020-01-07|website=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Twitter|movie_Ram}}\n* {{IMDb title|11449482}}\n\n{{Jeethu Joseph}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2020s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 film directed by Jeethu Joseph}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ram\n| image          = Ram Movie first look.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Announcement poster \n| director       = [[Jeethu Joseph]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Ramesh P. Pillai\n* Sudhan S. Pillai\n}}\n| writer         = Jeethu Joseph\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Mohanlal]]\n* [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]]\n* [[Indrajith Sukumaran]]\n}}\n| music          = Vishnu Shyam\n| cinematography = [[Satheesh Kurup]]\n| editing        = V. S. Vinayak\n| studio         = {{plainlist|\n* Abhishek Films\n* Passion Studios\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Maxlab Cinemas and Entertainments]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|10|22}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Malayalam\n| budget         = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| gross          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n\n'''''Ram''''' is an upcoming Indian [[Malayalam]]-language [[action thriller]] film written and directed by [[Jeethu Joseph]] and produced by Abhishek Films and Passion Studios. The film stars [[Mohanlal]] in the title role, while [[Trisha]] making her second venture in [[Mollywood]] as the female lead opposite to Lal.<ref>https://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/news/mohanlal-trisha-krishnan-raam-jeethu-joseph-anoop-menon-1.4489775 </ref> [[Indrajith Sukumaran]], [[Adil Hussain]], Durga Krishnan and [[Saikumar (actor)|Saikumar]] playing important supporting roles. The film's music was composed by debutant Vishnu Shyam.\n\n[[Principal photography]] of the film began on 5 January 2020 in [[Kochi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/mohanlal-looks-super-cool-and-stylish-as-he-shoots-for-ram/articleshow/73274437.cms|title=Mohanlal looks super cool and stylish as he shoots for 'RAM' - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref> The crew are planning to shoot the film in [[Kochi]], [[Delhi]], [[Dhanushkodi]], [[Chennai]